56static QCString makeQualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters(const ClassDef *cd,
57 const ArgumentLists *actualParams,uint *actualParamIndex)
58{
59 //bool optimizeOutputJava = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_JAVA);
60 bool hideScopeNames = Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES);
61 //printf("qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters() localName=%s\n",qPrint(localName()));
62 QCString scName;
63 const Definition *d=cd->getOuterScope();
64 if (d)
65 {
66 if (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass)
67 {
68 const ClassDef *ocd=toClassDef(d);
69 scName = ocd->qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters(actualParams,actualParamIndex);
70 }
71 else if (!hideScopeNames)
72 {
73 scName = d->qualifiedName();
74 }
75 }
76
77 SrcLangExt lang = cd->getLanguage();
78 QCString scopeSeparator = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang);
79 if (!scName.isEmpty()) scName+=scopeSeparator;
80
81 bool isSpecialization = cd->localName().find('<')!=-1;
82
83 QCString clName = cd->className();
84 scName+=clName;
85 if (!cd->templateArguments().empty())
86 {
87 if (actualParams && *actualParamIndex<actualParams->size())
88 {
89 const ArgumentList &al = actualParams->at(*actualParamIndex);
90 if (!isSpecialization)
91 {
92 scName+=tempArgListToString(al,lang);
93 }
94 (*actualParamIndex)++;
95 }
96 else
97 {
98 if (!isSpecialization)
99 {
100 scName+=tempArgListToString(cd->templateArguments(),lang);
101 }
102 }
103 }
104 //printf("qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters: scope=%s qualifiedName=%s\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(scName));
105 return scName;
106}
107
108static QCString makeDisplayName(const ClassDef *cd,bool includeScope)
109{
110 //bool optimizeOutputForJava = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_JAVA);
111 SrcLangExt lang = cd->getLanguage();
112 //bool vhdlOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_VHDL);
113 QCString n;
114 if (lang==SrcLangExt_VHDL)
115 {
116 n = VhdlDocGen::getClassName(cd);
117 }
118 else
119 {
120 if (includeScope)
121 {
122 n=cd->qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters();
123 }
124 else
125 {
126 n=cd->className();
127 }
128 }
129 if (cd->isAnonymous())
130 {
131 n = removeAnonymousScopes(n);
132 }
133 QCString sep=getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang);
134 if (sep!="::")
135 {
136 n=substitute(n,"::",sep);
137 }
138 if (cd->compoundType()==ClassDef::Protocol && n.endsWith("-p"))
139 {
140 n="<"+n.left(n.length()-2)+">";
141 }
142 return n;
143}

593 return acd;
594}

605 const QCString &ctStr, const QCString &fName);
606
607 /*! file name that forms the base for the output file containing the
608 * class documentation. For compatibility with Qt (e.g. links via tag
609 * files) this name cannot be derived from the class name directly.
610 */
611 QCString fileName;
612
613 /*! file name used for the list of all members */
614 QCString memberListFileName;
615
616 /*! file name used for the collaboration diagram */
617 QCString collabFileName;
618
619 /*! file name used for the inheritance graph */
620 QCString inheritFileName;
621
622 /*! Include information about the header file should be included
623 * in the documentation. 0 by default, set by setIncludeFile().
624 */
625 std::unique_ptr<IncludeInfo> incInfo;
626
627 /*! List of base class (or super-classes) from which this class derives
628 * directly.
629 */
630 BaseClassList inherits;
631
632 /*! List of sub-classes that directly derive from this class
633 */
634 BaseClassList inheritedBy;
635
636 /*! Namespace this class is part of
637 * (this is the inner most namespace in case of nested namespaces)
638 */
639 //NamespaceDef *nspace = 0;
640
641 /*! File this class is defined in */
642 FileDef *fileDef = 0;
643
644 /*! List of all members (including inherited members) */
645 MemberNameInfoLinkedMap allMemberNameInfoLinkedMap;
646
647 /*! Template arguments of this class */
648 ArgumentList tempArgs;
649
650 /*! Type constraints for template parameters */
651 ArgumentList typeConstraints;
652
653 /*! Files that were used for generating the class documentation. */
654 FileList files;
655
656 /*! Examples that use this class */
657 ExampleList examples;
658
659 /*! Holds the kind of "class" this is. */
660 ClassDef::CompoundType compType;
661
662 /*! The protection level in which this class was found.
663 * Typically Public, but for nested classes this can also be Protected
664 * or Private.
665 */
666 Protection prot;
667
668 /*! The inner classes contained in this class. Will be 0 if there are
669 * no inner classes.
670 */
671 ClassLinkedRefMap innerClasses;
672
673 /* classes for the collaboration diagram */
674 UsesClassList usesImplClassList;
675 UsesClassList usedByImplClassList;
676
677 ConstraintClassList constraintClassList;
678
679 /*! Template instances that exists of this class, the key in the
680 * dictionary is the template argument list.
681 */
682 TemplateInstanceList templateInstances;
683
684 TemplateNameMap templBaseClassNames;
685
686 /*! The class this class is an instance of. */
687 const ClassDef *templateMaster = 0;
688
689 /*! local class name which could be a typedef'ed alias name. */
690 QCString className;
691
692 /*! If this class is a Objective-C category, then this points to the
693 * class which is extended.
694 */
695 ClassDef *categoryOf = 0;
696
697 MemberLists memberLists;
698
699 /* user defined member groups */
700 MemberGroupList memberGroups;
701
702 /*! Is this an abstract class? */
703 bool isAbstract = false;
704
705 /*! Is the class part of an unnamed namespace? */
706 bool isStatic = false;
707
708 /*! TRUE if classes members are merged with those of the base classes. */
709 bool membersMerged = false;
710
711 /*! TRUE if the class is defined in a source file rather than a header file. */
712 bool isLocal = false;
713
714 bool isTemplArg = false;
715
716 /*! Does this class group its user-grouped members
717 * as a sub-section of the normal (public/protected/..)
718 * groups?
719 */
720 bool subGrouping = false;
721
722 /** Reason of existence is a "use" relation */
723 bool usedOnly = false;
724
725 /** List of titles to use for the summary */
726 StringSet vhdlSummaryTitles;
727
728 /** Is this a simple (non-nested) C structure? */
729 bool isSimple = false;
730
731 /** Does this class overloaded the -> operator? */
732 const MemberDef *arrowOperator = 0;
733
734 const ClassDef *tagLessRef = 0;
735
736 /** Does this class represent a Java style enum? */
737 bool isJavaEnum = false;
738
739 uint64 spec = 0;
740
741 QCString metaData;
742
743 /** C++20 requires clause */
744 QCString requiresClause;
745
746 StringVector qualifiers;
747};

749void ClassDefImpl::IMPL::init(const QCString &defFileName, const QCString &name,
750 const QCString &ctStr, const QCString &fName)
751{
752 if (!fName.isEmpty())
753 {
754 fileName=stripExtension(fName);
755 }
756 else
757 {
758 fileName=ctStr+name;
759 }
760 prot=Protection::Public;
761 //nspace=0;
762 fileDef=0;
763 subGrouping=Config_getBool(SUBGROUPING);
764 templateMaster =0;
765 isAbstract = FALSE;
766 isStatic = FALSE;
767 isTemplArg = FALSE;
768 membersMerged = FALSE;
769 categoryOf = 0;
770 usedOnly = FALSE;
771 isSimple = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
772 arrowOperator = 0;
773 tagLessRef = 0;
774 spec=0;
775 //QCString ns;
776 //extractNamespaceName(name,className,ns);
777 //printf("m_name=%s m_className=%s ns=%s\n",qPrint(m_name),qPrint(m_className),qPrint(ns));
778
779 // we cannot use getLanguage at this point, as setLanguage has not been called.
780 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguageFromFileName(defFileName);
781 if ((lang==SrcLangExt_Cpp || lang==SrcLangExt_ObjC) &&
782 guessSection(defFileName)==Entry::SOURCE_SEC)
783 {
784 isLocal=TRUE;
785 }
786 else
787 {
788 isLocal=FALSE;
789 }
790}

881// adds new member definition to the class
882void ClassDefImpl::internalInsertMember(MemberDef *md,
883 Protection prot,
884 bool addToAllList
885 )
886{
887 //printf("insertInternalMember(%s) isHidden()=%d\n",qPrint(md->name()),md->isHidden());
888 if (md->isHidden()) return;
889
890 if (getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_VHDL)
891 {
892 QCString title=theTranslator->trVhdlType(md->getMemberSpecifiers(),FALSE);
893 m_impl->vhdlSummaryTitles.insert(title.str());
894 }
895
896 if (1 /*!isReference()*/) // changed to 1 for showing members of external
897 // classes when HAVE_DOT and UML_LOOK are enabled.
898 {
899 bool isSimple=FALSE;
900
901 /********************************************/
902 /* insert member in the declaration section */
903 /********************************************/
904 if (md->isRelated() && protectionLevelVisible(prot))
905 {
906 addMemberToList(MemberListType_related,md,TRUE);
907 }
908 else if (md->isFriend())
909 {
910 addMemberToList(MemberListType_friends,md,TRUE);
911 }
912 else
913 {
914 switch (md->memberType())
915 {
916 case MemberType_Service: // UNO IDL
917 addMemberToList(MemberListType_services,md,TRUE);
918 break;
919 case MemberType_Interface: // UNO IDL
920 addMemberToList(MemberListType_interfaces,md,TRUE);
921 break;
922 case MemberType_Signal: // Qt specific
923 addMemberToList(MemberListType_signals,md,TRUE);
924 break;
925 case MemberType_DCOP: // KDE2 specific
926 addMemberToList(MemberListType_dcopMethods,md,TRUE);
927 break;
928 case MemberType_Property:
929 addMemberToList(MemberListType_properties,md,TRUE);
930 break;
931 case MemberType_Event:
932 addMemberToList(MemberListType_events,md,TRUE);
933 break;
934 case MemberType_Slot: // Qt specific
935 switch (prot)
936 {
937 case Protection::Protected:
938 case Protection::Package: // slots in packages are not possible!
939 addMemberToList(MemberListType_proSlots,md,TRUE);
940 break;
941 case Protection::Public:
942 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubSlots,md,TRUE);
943 break;
944 case Protection::Private:
945 addMemberToList(MemberListType_priSlots,md,TRUE);
946 break;
947 }
948 break;
949 default: // any of the other members
950 if (md->isStatic())
951 {
952 if (md->isVariable())
953 {
954 switch (prot)
955 {
956 case Protection::Protected:
957 addMemberToList(MemberListType_proStaticAttribs,md,TRUE);
958 break;
959 case Protection::Package:
960 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pacStaticAttribs,md,TRUE);
961 break;
962 case Protection::Public:
963 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubStaticAttribs,md,TRUE);
964 break;
965 case Protection::Private:
966 addMemberToList(MemberListType_priStaticAttribs,md,TRUE);
967 break;
968 }
969 }
970 else // function
971 {
972 switch (prot)
973 {
974 case Protection::Protected:
975 addMemberToList(MemberListType_proStaticMethods,md,TRUE);
976 break;
977 case Protection::Package:
978 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pacStaticMethods,md,TRUE);
979 break;
980 case Protection::Public:
981 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubStaticMethods,md,TRUE);
982 break;
983 case Protection::Private:
984 addMemberToList(MemberListType_priStaticMethods,md,TRUE);
985 break;
986 }
987 }
988 }
989 else // not static
990 {
991 if (md->isVariable())
992 {
993 switch (prot)
994 {
995 case Protection::Protected:
996 addMemberToList(MemberListType_proAttribs,md,TRUE);
997 break;
998 case Protection::Package:
999 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pacAttribs,md,TRUE);
1000 break;
1001 case Protection::Public:
1002 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubAttribs,md,TRUE);
1003 isSimple=!md->isFunctionPtr();
1004 break;
1005 case Protection::Private:
1006 addMemberToList(MemberListType_priAttribs,md,TRUE);
1007 break;
1008 }
1009 }
1010 else if (md->isTypedef() || md->isEnumerate() || md->isEnumValue())
1011 {
1012 switch (prot)
1013 {
1014 case Protection::Protected:
1015 addMemberToList(MemberListType_proTypes,md,TRUE);
1016 break;
1017 case Protection::Package:
1018 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pacTypes,md,TRUE);
1019 break;
1020 case Protection::Public:
1021 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubTypes,md,TRUE);
1022 isSimple=!md->isEnumerate() &&
1023 !md->isEnumValue() &&
1024 QCString(md->typeString()).find(")(")==-1; // func ptr typedef
1025 break;
1026 case Protection::Private:
1027 addMemberToList(MemberListType_priTypes,md,TRUE);
1028 break;
1029 }
1030 }
1031 else // member function
1032 {
1033 switch (prot)
1034 {
1035 case Protection::Protected:
1036 addMemberToList(MemberListType_proMethods,md,TRUE);
1037 break;
1038 case Protection::Package:
1039 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pacMethods,md,TRUE);
1040 break;
1041 case Protection::Public:
1042 addMemberToList(MemberListType_pubMethods,md,TRUE);
1043 break;
1044 case Protection::Private:
1045 addMemberToList(MemberListType_priMethods,md,TRUE);
1046 break;
1047 }
1048 }
1049 }
1050 break;
1051 }
1052 }
1053 if (!isSimple) // not a simple field -> not a simple struct
1054 {
1055 m_impl->isSimple = FALSE;
1056 }
1057 //printf("adding %s simple=%d total_simple=%d\n",qPrint(name()),isSimple,m_impl->isSimple);
1058
1059 /*******************************************************/
1060 /* insert member in the detailed documentation section */
1061 /*******************************************************/
1062 if ((md->isRelated() && protectionLevelVisible(prot)) || md->isFriend())
1063 {
1064 addMemberToList(MemberListType_relatedMembers,md,FALSE);
1065 }
1066 else if (md->isFunction() &&
1067 md->protection()==Protection::Private &&
1068 (md->virtualness()!=Specifier::Normal || md->isOverride() || md->isFinal()) &&
1069 Config_getBool(EXTRACT_PRIV_VIRTUAL))
1070 {
1071 addMemberToList(MemberListType_functionMembers,md,FALSE);
1072 }
1073 else
1074 {
1075 switch (md->memberType())
1076 {
1077 case MemberType_Service: // UNO IDL
1078 addMemberToList(MemberListType_serviceMembers,md,FALSE);
1079 break;
1080 case MemberType_Interface: // UNO IDL
1081 addMemberToList(MemberListType_interfaceMembers,md,FALSE);
1082 break;
1083 case MemberType_Property:
1084 addMemberToList(MemberListType_propertyMembers,md,FALSE);
1085 break;
1086 case MemberType_Event:
1087 addMemberToList(MemberListType_eventMembers,md,FALSE);
1088 break;
1089 case MemberType_Signal: // fall through
1090 case MemberType_DCOP:
1091 addMemberToList(MemberListType_functionMembers,md,FALSE);
1092 break;
1093 case MemberType_Slot:
1094 if (protectionLevelVisible(prot))
1095 {
1096 addMemberToList(MemberListType_functionMembers,md,FALSE);
1097 }
1098 break;
1099 default: // any of the other members
1100 if (protectionLevelVisible(prot))
1101 {
1102 switch (md->memberType())
1103 {
1104 case MemberType_Typedef:
1105 addMemberToList(MemberListType_typedefMembers,md,FALSE);
1106 break;
1107 case MemberType_Enumeration:
1108 addMemberToList(MemberListType_enumMembers,md,FALSE);
1109 break;
1110 case MemberType_EnumValue:
1111 addMemberToList(MemberListType_enumValMembers,md,FALSE);
1112 break;
1113 case MemberType_Function:
1114 if (md->isConstructor() || md->isDestructor())
1115 {
1116 m_impl->memberLists.get(MemberListType_constructors,MemberListContainer::Class)->push_back(md);
1117 }
1118 else
1119 {
1120 addMemberToList(MemberListType_functionMembers,md,FALSE);
1121 }
1122 break;
1123 case MemberType_Variable:
1124 addMemberToList(MemberListType_variableMembers,md,FALSE);
1125 break;
1126 case MemberType_Define:
1127 warn(md->getDefFileName(),md->getDefLine()-1,"A define (%s) cannot be made a member of %s",
1128 qPrint(md->name()), qPrint(this->name()));
1129 break;
1130 default:
1131 err("Unexpected member type %d found!\n",md->memberType());
1132 }
1133 }
1134 break;
1135 }
1136 }
1137
1138 /*************************************************/
1139 /* insert member in the appropriate member group */
1140 /*************************************************/
1141 // Note: this must be done AFTER inserting the member in the
1142 // regular groups
1143 //addMemberToGroup(md,groupId);
1144
1145 }
1146
1147 if (md->virtualness()==Specifier::Pure)
1148 {
1149 m_impl->isAbstract=true;
1150 }
1151
1152 if (md->name()=="operator->")
1153 {
1154 m_impl->arrowOperator=md;
1155 }
1156
1157 if (addToAllList &&
1158 !(Config_getBool(HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS) &&
1159 md->isFriend() &&
1160 (QCString(md->typeString())=="friend class" ||
1161 QCString(md->typeString())=="friend struct" ||
1162 QCString(md->typeString())=="friend union")))
1163 {
1164 //printf("=======> adding member %s to class %s\n",qPrint(md->name()),qPrint(name()));
1165
1166 MemberNameInfo *mni = m_impl->allMemberNameInfoLinkedMap.add(md->name());
1167 mni->push_back(std::make_unique<MemberInfo>(md,prot,md->virtualness(),FALSE));
1168 }
1169}

1173 internalInsertMember(md,md->protection(),TRUE);

1238static void writeInheritanceSpecifier(OutputList &ol,const BaseClassDef &bcd)
1239{
1240 if (bcd.prot!=Protection::Public || bcd.virt!=Specifier::Normal)
1241 {
1242 ol.startTypewriter();
1243 ol.docify(" [");
1244 StringVector sl;
1245 if (bcd.prot==Protection::Protected) sl.push_back("protected");
1246 else if (bcd.prot==Protection::Private) sl.push_back("private");
1247 if (bcd.virt==Specifier::Virtual) sl.push_back("virtual");
1248 bool first=true;
1249 for (const auto &s : sl)
1250 {
1251 if (!first) ol.docify(", ");
1252 ol.docify(s.c_str());
1253 first=false;
1254 }
1255 ol.docify("]");
1256 ol.endTypewriter();
1257 }
1258}

1260void ClassDefImpl::setIncludeFile(FileDef *fd,
1261 const QCString &includeName,bool local, bool force)
1262{
1263 //printf("ClassDefImpl::setIncludeFile(%p,%s,%d,%d)\n",fd,includeName,local,force);
1264 if (!m_impl->incInfo) m_impl->incInfo = std::make_unique<IncludeInfo>();
1265 if ((!includeName.isEmpty() && m_impl->incInfo->includeName.isEmpty()) ||
1266 (fd!=0 && m_impl->incInfo->fileDef==0)
1267 )
1268 {
1269 //printf("Setting file info\n");
1270 m_impl->incInfo->fileDef = fd;
1271 m_impl->incInfo->includeName = includeName;
1272 m_impl->incInfo->local = local;
1273 }
1274 if (force && !includeName.isEmpty())
1275 {
1276 m_impl->incInfo->includeName = includeName;
1277 m_impl->incInfo->local = local;
1278 }
1279}

1299static void searchTemplateSpecs(/*in*/ const Definition *d,
1300 /*out*/ ArgumentLists &result,
1301 /*out*/ QCString &name,
1302 /*in*/ SrcLangExt lang)
1303{
1304 if (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass)
1305 {
1306 if (d->getOuterScope())
1307 {
1308 searchTemplateSpecs(d->getOuterScope(),result,name,lang);
1309 }
1310 const ClassDef *cd=toClassDef(d);
1311 if (!name.isEmpty()) name+="::";
1312 QCString clName = d->localName();
1313 if (clName.endsWith("-p"))
1314 {
1315 clName = clName.left(clName.length()-2);
1316 }
1317 name+=clName;
1318 bool isSpecialization = d->localName().find('<')!=-1;
1319 if (!cd->templateArguments().empty())
1320 {
1321 result.push_back(cd->templateArguments());
1322 if (!isSpecialization)
1323 {
1324 name+=tempArgListToString(cd->templateArguments(),lang);
1325 }
1326 }
1327 }
1328 else
1329 {
1330 name+=d->qualifiedName();
1331 }
1332}
1333
1334void ClassDefImpl::writeTemplateSpec(OutputList &ol,const Definition *d,
1335 const QCString &type,SrcLangExt lang) const
1336{
1337 ArgumentLists specs;
1338 QCString name;
1339 searchTemplateSpecs(d,specs,name,lang);
1340 if (!specs.empty()) // class has template scope specifiers
1341 {
1342 ol.startCompoundTemplateParams();
1343 for (const ArgumentList &al : specs)
1344 {
1345 ol.docify("template<");
1346 auto it = al.begin();
1347 while (it!=al.end())
1348 {
1349 Argument a = *it;
1350 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
1351 d, // scope
1352 getFileDef(), // fileScope
1353 this, // self
1354 a.type, // text
1355 FALSE // autoBreak
1356 );
1357 if (!a.name.isEmpty())
1358 {
1359 ol.docify(" ");
1360 ol.docify(a.name);
1361 }
1362 if (a.defval.length()!=0)
1363 {
1364 ol.docify(" = ");
1365 ol.docify(a.defval);
1366 }
1367 ++it;
1368 if (it!=al.end()) ol.docify(", ");
1369 }
1370 ol.docify(">");
1371 ol.lineBreak();
1372 }
1373 if (!m_impl->requiresClause.isEmpty())
1374 {
1375 ol.docify("requires ");
1376 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
1377 d, // scope
1378 getFileDef(), // fileScope
1379 this, // self
1380 m_impl->requiresClause, // text
1381 FALSE // autoBreak
1382 );

1384 }
1385 ol.docify(type.lower()+" "+name);
1386 ol.endCompoundTemplateParams();
1387 }

1418void ClassDefImpl::writeDetailedDocumentationBody(OutputList &ol) const
1419{
1420 bool repeatBrief = Config_getBool(REPEAT_BRIEF);
1421
1422 ol.startTextBlock();
1423
1424 if (getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Cpp)
1425 {
1426 writeTemplateSpec(ol,this,compoundTypeString(),getLanguage());
1427 }
1428

1431 {

1433 QCString(),FALSE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT));

1436 !documentation().isEmpty())

1447 QCString(),FALSE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT));

1451
1452 // write examples
1453 if (hasExamples())
1454 {
1455 ol.startExamples();
1456 ol.startDescForItem();
1457 //ol.startParagraph();
1458 writeExamples(ol,m_impl->examples);
1459 //ol.endParagraph();
1460 ol.endDescForItem();
1461 ol.endExamples();
1462 }
1463 //ol.newParagraph();
1464 writeSourceDef(ol,name());
1465 ol.endTextBlock();
1466}

1514QCString ClassDefImpl::generatedFromFiles() const
1515{
1516 QCString result;
1517 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
1518 size_t numFiles = m_impl->files.size();
1519 if (lang==SrcLangExt_Fortran)
1520 {
1521 result = theTranslator->trGeneratedFromFilesFortran(
1522 getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_ObjC && m_impl->compType==Interface ? Class : m_impl->compType,
1523 numFiles==1);
1524 }
1525 else if (isJavaEnum())
1526 {
1527 result = theTranslator->trEnumGeneratedFromFiles(numFiles==1);
1528 }
1529 else if (m_impl->compType==Service)
1530 {
1531 result = theTranslator->trServiceGeneratedFromFiles(numFiles==1);
1532 }
1533 else if (m_impl->compType==Singleton)
1534 {
1535 result = theTranslator->trSingletonGeneratedFromFiles(numFiles==1);
1536 }
1537 else
1538 {
1539 result = theTranslator->trGeneratedFromFiles(
1540 getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_ObjC && m_impl->compType==Interface ? Class : m_impl->compType,
1541 numFiles==1);
1542 }
1543 return result;

1546void ClassDefImpl::showUsedFiles(OutputList &ol) const
1547{
1548 ol.pushGeneratorState();
1549 ol.disable(OutputType::Man);
1550
1551
1552 ol.writeRuler();
1553 ol.pushGeneratorState();
1554 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Docbook);
1555 ol.startParagraph();
1556 ol.parseText(generatedFromFiles());
1557 ol.endParagraph();
1558 ol.popGeneratorState();
1559 ol.disable(OutputType::Docbook);
1560 ol.parseText(generatedFromFiles());
1561 ol.enable(OutputType::Docbook);
1562
1563 bool first=TRUE;
1564 for (const auto &fd : m_impl->files)
1565 {
1566 if (first)
1567 {
1568 first=FALSE;

1570 }
1571

1574 if (Config_getBool(FULL_PATH_NAMES))

1578

1581 {
1582 fname += " (" + fd->getVersion() + ")";
1583 }
1584
1585 // for HTML
1586 ol.pushGeneratorState();
1587 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Html);
1588 if (fd->generateSourceFile())
1589 {
1590 ol.writeObjectLink(QCString(),fd->getSourceFileBase(),QCString(),fname);
1591 }
1592 else if (fd->isLinkable())
1593 {
1594 ol.writeObjectLink(fd->getReference(),fd->getOutputFileBase(),QCString(),fname);
1595 }
1596 else
1597 {
1598 ol.docify(fname);
1599 }
1600 ol.popGeneratorState();
1601
1602 // for other output formats
1603 ol.pushGeneratorState();
1604 ol.disable(OutputType::Html);
1605 if (fd->isLinkable())
1606 {
1607 ol.writeObjectLink(fd->getReference(),fd->getOutputFileBase(),QCString(),fname);
1608 }
1609 else
1610 {
1611 ol.docify(fname);
1612 }
1613 ol.popGeneratorState();
1614
1615 ol.endItemListItem();
1616 }
1617 if (!first) ol.endItemList();
1618
1619 ol.popGeneratorState();
1620}

1622int ClassDefImpl::countInheritanceNodes() const
1623{
1624 int count=0;
1625 for (const auto &ibcd : m_impl->inheritedBy)
1626 {
1627 const ClassDef *icd=ibcd.classDef;
1628 if ( icd->isVisibleInHierarchy()) count++;
1629 }
1630 for (const auto &ibcd : m_impl->inherits)
1631 {
1632 const ClassDef *icd=ibcd.classDef;
1633 if ( icd->isVisibleInHierarchy()) count++;
1634 }
1635 return count;
1636}
1637
1638void ClassDefImpl::writeInheritanceGraph(OutputList &ol) const
1639{
1640 bool haveDot = Config_getBool(HAVE_DOT);
1641 auto classGraph = Config_getEnum(CLASS_GRAPH);
1642
1643 if (classGraph == CLASS_GRAPH_t::NO) return;
1644 // count direct inheritance relations
1645 const int count=countInheritanceNodes();
1646
1647 bool renderDiagram = FALSE;
1648 if (haveDot && (classGraph==CLASS_GRAPH_t::YES || classGraph==CLASS_GRAPH_t::GRAPH))
1649 // write class diagram using dot
1650 {
1651 DotClassGraph inheritanceGraph(this,Inheritance);
1652 if (inheritanceGraph.isTooBig())
1653 {
1654 warn_uncond("Inheritance graph for '%s' not generated, too many nodes (%d), threshold is %d. Consider increasing DOT_GRAPH_MAX_NODES.\n",
1655 qPrint(name()), inheritanceGraph.numNodes(), Config_getInt(DOT_GRAPH_MAX_NODES));
1656 }
1657 else if (!inheritanceGraph.isTrivial())
1658 {
1659 ol.pushGeneratorState();
1660 ol.disable(OutputType::Man);
1661 ol.startDotGraph();
1662 ol.parseText(theTranslator->trClassDiagram(displayName()));
1663 ol.endDotGraph(inheritanceGraph);
1664 ol.popGeneratorState();
1665 renderDiagram = TRUE;
1666 }
1667 }
1668 else if ((classGraph==CLASS_GRAPH_t::YES || classGraph==CLASS_GRAPH_t::GRAPH) && count>0)
1669 // write class diagram using built-in generator
1670 {
1671 ClassDiagram diagram(this); // create a diagram of this class.
1672 ol.startClassDiagram();
1673 ol.disable(OutputType::Man);
1674 ol.parseText(theTranslator->trClassDiagram(displayName()));
1675 ol.enable(OutputType::Man);
1676 ol.endClassDiagram(diagram,getOutputFileBase(),displayName());
1677 renderDiagram = TRUE;
1678 }
1679
1680 if (renderDiagram) // if we already show the inheritance relations graphically,
1681 // then hide the text version
1682 {
1683 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Man);
1684 }
1685
1686 if (!m_impl->inherits.empty())
1687 {
1688 auto replaceFunc = [this,&ol](size_t entryIndex)
1689 {
1690 BaseClassDef &bcd=m_impl->inherits[entryIndex];
1691 ClassDef *cd=bcd.classDef;
1692
1693 // use the class name but with the template arguments as given
1694 // in the inheritance relation
1695 QCString displayName = insertTemplateSpecifierInScope(
1696 cd->displayName(),bcd.templSpecifiers);
1697
1698 if (cd->isLinkable())
1699 {
1700 ol.writeObjectLink(cd->getReference(),
1701 cd->getOutputFileBase(),
1702 cd->anchor(),
1703 displayName);
1704 }
1705 else
1706 {
1707 ol.docify(displayName);
1708 }
1709 };
1710
1711 ol.startParagraph();
1712 writeMarkerList(ol,
1713 theTranslator->trInheritsList(static_cast<int>(m_impl->inherits.size())).str(),
1714 m_impl->inherits.size(),
1715 replaceFunc);
1716 ol.endParagraph();
1717 }
1718
1719 // write subclasses
1720 if (!m_impl->inheritedBy.empty())
1721 {
1722
1723 auto replaceFunc = [this,&ol](size_t entryIndex)
1724 {
1725 BaseClassDef &bcd=m_impl->inheritedBy[entryIndex];
1726 ClassDef *cd=bcd.classDef;
1727 if (cd->isLinkable())
1728 {
1729 ol.writeObjectLink(cd->getReference(),cd->getOutputFileBase(),cd->anchor(),cd->displayName());
1730 }
1731 else
1732 {
1733 ol.docify(cd->displayName());
1734 }
1735 writeInheritanceSpecifier(ol,bcd);
1736 };
1737
1738 ol.startParagraph();
1739 writeMarkerList(ol,
1740 theTranslator->trInheritedByList(static_cast<int>(m_impl->inheritedBy.size())).str(),
1741 m_impl->inheritedBy.size(),
1742 replaceFunc);
1743 ol.endParagraph();
1744 }
1745
1746 if (renderDiagram)
1747 {
1748 ol.enableAll();
1749 }
1750}

1786
1787void ClassDefImpl::writeIncludeFilesForSlice(OutputList &ol) const
1788{
1789 if (m_impl->incInfo)
1790 {
1791 QCString nm;
1792 const StringVector &paths = Config_getList(STRIP_FROM_PATH);
1793 if (!paths.empty() && m_impl->incInfo->fileDef)
1794 {
1795 QCString abs = m_impl->incInfo->fileDef->absFilePath();
1796 QCString potential;
1797 unsigned int length = 0;
1798 for (const auto &s : paths)
1799 {
1800 FileInfo info(s);
1801 if (info.exists())
1802 {
1803 QCString prefix = info.absFilePath();
1804 if (prefix.at(prefix.length() - 1) != '/')
1805 {
1806 prefix += '/';
1807 }
1808
1809 if (prefix.length() > length &&
1810 qstricmp(abs.left(prefix.length()).data(), prefix.data()) == 0) // case insensitive compare
1811 {
1812 length = prefix.length();
1813 potential = abs.right(abs.length() - prefix.length());
1814 }
1815 }
1816 }
1817
1818 if (length > 0)
1819 {
1820 nm = potential;
1821 }
1822 }
1823
1824 if (nm.isEmpty())
1825 {
1826 nm = m_impl->incInfo->includeName;
1827 }
1828
1829 ol.startParagraph();
1830 ol.docify(theTranslator->trDefinedIn()+" ");
1831 ol.startTypewriter();
1832 ol.docify("<");
1833 if (m_impl->incInfo->fileDef)
1834 {
1835 ol.writeObjectLink(QCString(),m_impl->incInfo->fileDef->includeName(),QCString(),nm);
1836 }
1837 else
1838 {
1839 ol.docify(nm);
1840 }
1841 ol.docify(">");
1842 ol.endTypewriter();
1843 ol.endParagraph();
1844 }
1845
1846 // Write a summary of the Slice definition including metadata.
1847 ol.startParagraph();
1848 ol.startTypewriter();
1849 if (!m_impl->metaData.isEmpty())
1850 {
1851 ol.docify(m_impl->metaData);
1852 ol.lineBreak();
1853 }
1854 if (m_impl->spec & Entry::Local)
1855 {
1856 ol.docify("local ");
1857 }
1858 if (m_impl->spec & Entry::Interface)
1859 {
1860 ol.docify("interface ");
1861 }
1862 else if (m_impl->spec & Entry::Struct)
1863 {
1864 ol.docify("struct ");
1865 }
1866 else if (m_impl->spec & Entry::Exception)
1867 {
1868 ol.docify("exception ");
1869 }
1870 else
1871 {
1872 ol.docify("class ");
1873 }
1874 ol.docify(stripScope(name()));
1875 if (!m_impl->inherits.empty())
1876 {
1877 if (m_impl->spec & (Entry::Interface|Entry::Exception))
1878 {
1879 ol.docify(" extends ");
1880 bool first=true;
1881 for (const auto &ibcd : m_impl->inherits)
1882 {
1883 if (!first) ol.docify(", ");
1884 ClassDef *icd = ibcd.classDef;
1885 ol.docify(icd->name());
1886 first=false;
1887 }
1888 }
1889 else
1890 {
1891 // Must be a class.
1892 bool implements = false;
1893 for (const auto &ibcd : m_impl->inherits)
1894 {
1895 ClassDef *icd = ibcd.classDef;
1896 if (icd->isInterface())
1897 {
1898 implements = true;
1899 }
1900 else
1901 {
1902 ol.docify(" extends ");
1903 ol.docify(icd->name());
1904 }
1905 }
1906 if (implements)
1907 {
1908 ol.docify(" implements ");
1909 bool first = true;
1910 for (const auto &ibcd : m_impl->inherits)
1911 {
1912 ClassDef *icd = ibcd.classDef;
1913 if (icd->isInterface())
1914 {
1915 if (!first) ol.docify(", ");
1916 first = false;
1917 ol.docify(icd->name());
1918 }
1919 }
1920 }
1921 }
1922 }
1923 ol.docify(" { ... }");
1924 ol.endTypewriter();
1925 ol.endParagraph();
1926}

2088 if (lmd)

2115void ClassDefImpl::writeTagFile(TextStream &tagFile) const
2116{
2117 if (!isLinkableInProject() || isArtificial()) return;
2118 tagFile << " <compound kind=\"";
2119 if (isFortran() && (compoundTypeString() == "type"))
2120 tagFile << "struct";
2121 else
2122 tagFile << compoundTypeString();
2123 tagFile << "\"";
2124 if (isObjectiveC()) { tagFile << " objc=\"yes\""; }
2125 tagFile << ">\n";
2126 tagFile << " <name>" << convertToXML(name()) << "</name>\n";
2127 tagFile << " <filename>" << convertToXML(addHtmlExtensionIfMissing(getOutputFileBase())) << "</filename>\n";
2128 if (!anchor().isEmpty())
2129 {
2130 tagFile << " <anchor>" << convertToXML(anchor()) << "</anchor>\n";
2131 }
2132 QCString idStr = id();
2133 if (!idStr.isEmpty())
2134 {
2135 tagFile << " <clangid>" << convertToXML(idStr) << "</clangid>\n";
2136 }
2137 for (const Argument &a : m_impl->tempArgs)
2138 {
2139 tagFile << " <templarg>" << convertToXML(a.type);
2140 if (!a.name.isEmpty())
2141 {
2142 tagFile << " " << convertToXML(a.name);
2143 }
2144 tagFile << "</templarg>\n";
2145 }
2146 for (const auto &ibcd : m_impl->inherits)
2147 {
2148 ClassDef *cd=ibcd.classDef;
2149 if (cd && cd->isLinkable())
2150 {
2151 if (!Config_getString(GENERATE_TAGFILE).isEmpty())
2152 {
2153 tagFile << " <base";
2154 if (ibcd.prot==Protection::Protected)
2155 {
2156 tagFile << " protection=\"protected\"";
2157 }
2158 else if (ibcd.prot==Protection::Private)
2159 {
2160 tagFile << " protection=\"private\"";
2161 }
2162 if (ibcd.virt==Specifier::Virtual)
2163 {
2164 tagFile << " virtualness=\"virtual\"";
2165 }
2166 tagFile << ">" << convertToXML(cd->name()) << "</base>\n";
2167 }
2168 }
2169 }
2170 for (const auto &lde : LayoutDocManager::instance().docEntries(LayoutDocManager::Class))
2171 {
2172 switch (lde->kind())
2173 {
2174 case LayoutDocEntry::ClassNestedClasses:
2175 {
2176 for (const auto &innerCd : m_impl->innerClasses)
2177 {
2178 if (innerCd->isLinkableInProject() && innerCd->templateMaster()==0 &&
2179 protectionLevelVisible(innerCd->protection()) &&
2180 !innerCd->isEmbeddedInOuterScope()
2181 )
2182 {
2183 tagFile << " <class kind=\"" << innerCd->compoundTypeString() <<
2184 "\">" << convertToXML(innerCd->name()) << "</class>\n";
2185 }
2186 }
2187 }
2188 break;
2189 case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDecl:
2190 {
2191 const LayoutDocEntryMemberDecl *lmd = dynamic_cast<const LayoutDocEntryMemberDecl*>(lde.get());
2192 if (lmd)
2193 {
2194 MemberList * ml = getMemberList(lmd->type);
2195 if (ml)
2196 {
2197 ml->writeTagFile(tagFile);
2198 }
2199 }
2200 }
2201 break;
2202 case LayoutDocEntry::MemberGroups:
2203 {
2204 for (const auto &mg : m_impl->memberGroups)
2205 {
2206 mg->writeTagFile(tagFile);
2207 }
2208 }
2209 break;
2210 default:
2211 break;
2212 }
2213 }
2214 writeDocAnchorsToTagFile(tagFile);
2215 tagFile << " </compound>\n";
2216}

2218/** Write class documentation inside another container (i.e. a group) */
2219void ClassDefImpl::writeInlineDocumentation(OutputList &ol) const
2220{
2221 bool isSimple = m_impl->isSimple;
2222
2223 ol.addIndexItem(name(),QCString());
2224 //printf("ClassDefImpl::writeInlineDocumentation(%s)\n",qPrint(name()));
2225
2226 // part 1: anchor and title
2227 QCString s = compoundTypeString()+" "+name();
2228
2229 // part 1a
2230 ol.pushGeneratorState();
2231 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Html);
2232 { // only HTML only
2233 ol.writeAnchor(QCString(),anchor());
2234 ol.startMemberDoc(QCString(),QCString(),anchor(),name(),1,1,FALSE);
2235 ol.startMemberDocName(FALSE);
2236 ol.parseText(s);
2237 ol.endMemberDocName();
2238 ol.endMemberDoc(FALSE);
2239 ol.writeString("</div>");
2240 ol.startIndent();
2241 }
2242 ol.popGeneratorState();
2243
2244 // part 1b
2245 ol.pushGeneratorState();
2246 ol.disable(OutputType::Html);
2247 ol.disable(OutputType::Man);
2248 { // for LaTeX/RTF only
2249 ol.writeAnchor(getOutputFileBase(),anchor());
2250 }
2251 ol.popGeneratorState();
2252
2253 // part 1c
2254 ol.pushGeneratorState();
2255 ol.disable(OutputType::Html);
2256 {
2257 // for LaTeX/RTF/Man
2258 ol.startGroupHeader(1);
2259 ol.parseText(s);
2260 ol.endGroupHeader(1);
2261 }
2262 ol.popGeneratorState();
2263
2264 SrcLangExt lang=getLanguage();
2265
2266 // part 2: the header and detailed description
2267 for (const auto &lde : LayoutDocManager::instance().docEntries(LayoutDocManager::Class))
2268 {
2269 switch (lde->kind())
2270 {
2271 case LayoutDocEntry::BriefDesc:
2272 {
2273 // since we already shown the brief description in the
2274 // declaration part of the container, so we use this to
2275 // show the details on top.
2276 writeDetailedDocumentationBody(ol);
2277 }
2278 break;
2279 case LayoutDocEntry::ClassInheritanceGraph:
2280 writeInheritanceGraph(ol);
2281 break;
2282 case LayoutDocEntry::ClassCollaborationGraph:
2283 writeCollaborationGraph(ol);
2284 break;
2285 case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDeclStart:
2286 if (!isSimple) startMemberDeclarations(ol);
2287 break;
2288 case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDecl:
2289 {
2290 const LayoutDocEntryMemberDecl *lmd = dynamic_cast<const LayoutDocEntryMemberDecl*>(lde.get());
2291 if (lmd)
2292 {
2293 ClassDefSet visitedClasses;
2294 if (!isSimple) writeMemberDeclarations(ol,visitedClasses,lmd->type,lmd->title(lang),lmd->subtitle(lang),TRUE);
2295 }
2296 }
2297 break;
2298 case LayoutDocEntry::MemberGroups:
2299 if (!isSimple) writeMemberGroups(ol,TRUE);
2300 break;
2301 case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDeclEnd:
2302 if (!isSimple) endMemberDeclarations(ol);
2303 break;
2304 case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDefStart:
2305 if (!isSimple) startMemberDocumentation(ol);
2306 break;
2307 case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDef:
2308 {
2309 const LayoutDocEntryMemberDef *lmd = dynamic_cast<const LayoutDocEntryMemberDef*>(lde.get());
2310 if (lmd)
2311 {
2312 if (isSimple)
2313 {
2314 writeSimpleMemberDocumentation(ol,lmd->type);
2315 }
2316 else
2317 {
2318 writeMemberDocumentation(ol,lmd->type,lmd->title(lang),TRUE);
2319 }
2320 }
2321 }
2322 break;
2323 case LayoutDocEntry::MemberDefEnd:
2324 if (!isSimple) endMemberDocumentation(ol);
2325 break;
2326 default:
2327 break;
2328 }
2329 }
2330
2331 // part 3: close the block
2332 ol.pushGeneratorState();
2333 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Html);
2334 { // HTML only
2335 ol.endIndent();
2336 }
2337 ol.popGeneratorState();
2338}

2396void ClassDefImpl::writeDeclarationLink(OutputList &ol,bool &found,const QCString &header,bool localNames) const
2397{
2398 //bool fortranOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_FOR_FORTRAN);
2399 //bool vhdlOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_VHDL);
2400 bool sliceOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_SLICE);
2401 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
2402 if (visibleInParentsDeclList())
2403 {
2404 if (!found) // first class
2405 {
2406 if (sliceOpt)
2407 {
2408 if (compoundType()==Interface)
2409 {
2410 ol.startMemberHeader("interfaces");
2411 }
2412 else if (compoundType()==Struct)
2413 {
2414 ol.startMemberHeader("structs");
2415 }
2416 else if (compoundType()==Exception)
2417 {
2418 ol.startMemberHeader("exceptions");
2419 }
2420 else // compoundType==Class
2421 {
2422 ol.startMemberHeader("nested-classes");
2423 }
2424 }
2425 else // non-Slice optimization: single header for class/struct/..
2426 {
2427 ol.startMemberHeader("nested-classes");
2428 }
2429 if (!header.isEmpty())
2430 {
2431 ol.parseText(header);
2432 }
2433 else if (lang==SrcLangExt_VHDL)
2434 {
2435 ol.parseText(theTranslator->trVhdlType(VhdlDocGen::ARCHITECTURE,FALSE));
2436 }
2437 else
2438 {
2439 ol.parseText(lang==SrcLangExt_Fortran ?
2440 theTranslator->trDataTypes() :
2441 theTranslator->trCompounds());
2442 }
2443 ol.endMemberHeader();
2444 ol.startMemberList();
2445 found=TRUE;
2446 }
2447 ol.startMemberDeclaration();
2448 ol.startMemberItem(anchor(),OutputGenerator::MemberItemType::Normal);
2449 QCString ctype = compoundTypeString();
2450 QCString cname = displayName(!localNames);
2451
2452 if (lang!=SrcLangExt_VHDL) // for VHDL we swap the name and the type
2453 {
2454 if (isSliceLocal())
2455 {
2456 ol.writeString("local ");
2457 }
2458 ol.writeString(ctype);
2459 ol.writeString(" ");
2460 ol.insertMemberAlign();
2461 }
2462 if (isLinkable())
2463 {
2464 ol.writeObjectLink(getReference(),
2465 getOutputFileBase(),
2466 anchor(),
2467 cname
2468 );
2469 }
2470 else
2471 {
2472 ol.startBold();
2473 ol.docify(cname);
2474 ol.endBold();
2475 }
2476 if (lang==SrcLangExt_VHDL) // now write the type
2477 {
2478 ol.writeString(" ");
2479 ol.insertMemberAlign();
2480 ol.writeString(VhdlDocGen::getProtectionName(VhdlDocGen::convert(protection())));
2481 }
2482 ol.endMemberItem(OutputGenerator::MemberItemType::Normal);
2483
2484 // add the brief description if available
2485 if (!briefDescription().isEmpty() && Config_getBool(BRIEF_MEMBER_DESC))
2486 {
2487 auto parser { createDocParser() };
2488 auto ast { validatingParseDoc(*parser.get(),
2489 briefFile(),briefLine(),this,0,
2490 briefDescription(),FALSE,FALSE,
2491 QCString(),TRUE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT)) };
2492 if (!ast->isEmpty())
2493 {
2494 ol.startMemberDescription(anchor());
2495 ol.writeDoc(ast.get(),this,0);
2496 if (isLinkableInProject())
2497 {
2498 writeMoreLink(ol,anchor());
2499 }
2500 ol.endMemberDescription();
2501 }
2502 }
2503 ol.endMemberDeclaration(anchor(),QCString());
2504 }
2505}

2507void ClassDefImpl::addClassAttributes(OutputList &ol) const
2508{
2509 StringVector sl;
2510 if (isFinal()) sl.push_back("final");
2511 if (isSealed()) sl.push_back("sealed");
2512 if (isAbstract()) sl.push_back("abstract");
2513 if (getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_IDL && isPublished()) sl.push_back("published");
2514
2515 for (const auto &sx : m_impl->qualifiers)
2516 {
2517 bool alreadyAdded = std::find(sl.begin(), sl.end(), sx) != sl.end();
2518 if (!alreadyAdded)
2519 {
2520 sl.push_back(sx);
2521 }
2522 }
2523
2524 ol.pushGeneratorState();
2525 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Html);
2526 if (!sl.empty())
2527 {
2528 ol.startLabels();
2529 size_t i=0;
2530 for (const auto &s : sl)
2531 {
2532 i++;
2533 ol.writeLabel(s.c_str(),i==sl.size());
2534 }
2535 ol.endLabels();
2536 }
2537 ol.popGeneratorState();
2538}

2682QCString ClassDefImpl::title() const
2683{
2684 QCString pageTitle;
2685 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
2686
2687 if (lang==SrcLangExt_Fortran)
2688 {
2689 pageTitle = theTranslator->trCompoundReferenceFortran(displayName(),
2690 m_impl->compType,
2691 !m_impl->tempArgs.empty());
2692 }
2693 else if (lang==SrcLangExt_Slice)
2694 {
2695 pageTitle = theTranslator->trCompoundReferenceSlice(displayName(),
2696 m_impl->compType,
2697 isSliceLocal());
2698 }
2699 else if (lang==SrcLangExt_VHDL)
2700 {
2701 pageTitle = theTranslator->trCustomReference(VhdlDocGen::getClassTitle(this));
2702 }
2703 else if (isJavaEnum())
2704 {
2705 pageTitle = theTranslator->trEnumReference(displayName());
2706 }
2707 else if (m_impl->compType==Service)
2708 {
2709 pageTitle = theTranslator->trServiceReference(displayName());
2710 }
2711 else if (m_impl->compType==Singleton)
2712 {
2713 pageTitle = theTranslator->trSingletonReference(displayName());
2714 }
2715 else
2716 {
2717 if (Config_getBool(HIDE_COMPOUND_REFERENCE))
2718 {
2719 pageTitle = displayName();
2720 }
2721 else
2722 {
2723 pageTitle = theTranslator->trCompoundReference(displayName(),
2724 m_impl->compType == Interface && getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_ObjC ? Class : m_impl->compType,
2725 !m_impl->tempArgs.empty());
2726 }
2727 }
2728 return pageTitle;
2729}

2731// write all documentation for this class
2732void ClassDefImpl::writeDocumentation(OutputList &ol) const
2733{
2734 bool generateTreeView = Config_getBool(GENERATE_TREEVIEW);
2735 //bool fortranOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_FOR_FORTRAN);
2736 //bool vhdlOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_VHDL);
2737 bool sliceOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_SLICE);
2738 QCString pageTitle = title();
2739
2740 HighlightedItem hli;
2741 if (sliceOpt)
2742 {
2743 if (compoundType()==Interface)
2744 {
2745 hli = HighlightedItem::InterfaceVisible;
2746 }
2747 else if (compoundType()==Struct)
2748 {
2749 hli = HighlightedItem::StructVisible;
2750 }
2751 else if (compoundType()==Exception)
2752 {
2753 hli = HighlightedItem::ExceptionVisible;
2754 }
2755 else
2756 {
2757 hli = HighlightedItem::ClassVisible;
2758 }
2759 }
2760 else
2761 {
2762 hli = HighlightedItem::ClassVisible;
2763 }
2764
2765 startFile(ol,getOutputFileBase(),name(),pageTitle,hli,!generateTreeView);
2766 if (!generateTreeView)
2767 {
2768 if (getOuterScope()!=Doxygen::globalScope)
2769 {
2770 writeNavigationPath(ol);
2771 }
2772 ol.endQuickIndices();
2773 }
2774
2775 startTitle(ol,getOutputFileBase(),this);
2776 ol.parseText(pageTitle);
2777 addClassAttributes(ol);
2778 addGroupListToTitle(ol,this);
2779 endTitle(ol,getOutputFileBase(),displayName());
2780 writeDocumentationContents(ol,pageTitle);
2781
2782 endFileWithNavPath(ol,this);
2783
2784 if (Config_getBool(SEPARATE_MEMBER_PAGES))
2785 {
2786 writeMemberPages(ol);
2787 }
2788}

2873// write the list of all (inherited) members for this class
2874void ClassDefImpl::writeMemberList(OutputList &ol) const
2875{
2876 bool cOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_FOR_C);
2877 //bool vhdlOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_VHDL);
2878 bool sliceOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_SLICE);
2879 bool generateTreeView = Config_getBool(GENERATE_TREEVIEW);
2880 if (m_impl->allMemberNameInfoLinkedMap.empty() || cOpt) return;
2881 // only for HTML
2882 ol.pushGeneratorState();
2883 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Html);
2884
2885 HighlightedItem hli;
2886 if (sliceOpt)
2887 {
2888 if (compoundType()==Interface)
2889 {
2890 hli = HighlightedItem::InterfaceVisible;
2891 }
2892 else if (compoundType()==Struct)
2893 {
2894 hli = HighlightedItem::StructVisible;
2895 }
2896 else if (compoundType()==Exception)

3244static bool hasNonReferenceSuperClassRec(const ClassDef *cd,int level)
3245{
3246 bool found=!cd->isReference() && cd->isLinkableInProject() && !cd->isHidden();
3247 if (found)
3248 {
3249 return TRUE; // we're done if this class is not a reference
3250 }
3251 for (const auto &ibcd : cd->subClasses())
3252 {
3253 const ClassDef *bcd=ibcd.classDef;
3254 if (level>256)
3255 {
3256 err("Possible recursive class relation while inside %s and looking for base class %s\n",qPrint(cd->name()),qPrint(bcd->name()));
3257 return FALSE;
3258 }
3259 // recurse into the super class branch
3260 found = found || hasNonReferenceSuperClassRec(bcd,level+1);
3261 if (!found)
3262 {
3263 // look for template instances that might have non-reference super classes
3264 for (const auto &cil : bcd->getTemplateInstances())
3265 {
3266 // recurse into the template instance branch
3267 found = hasNonReferenceSuperClassRec(cil.classDef,level+1);
3268 if (found) break;
3269 }
3270 }
3271 else
3272 {
3273 break;
3274 }
3275 }
3276 return found;
3277}

3282bool ClassDefImpl::hasNonReferenceSuperClass() const
3283{
3284 return hasNonReferenceSuperClassRec(this,0);

3408//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3409// recursive function:
3410// returns the distance to the base class definition 'bcd' represents an (in)direct base
3411// class of class definition 'cd' or 0 if it does not.
3412
3413int ClassDefImpl::isBaseClass(const ClassDef *bcd, bool followInstances,const QCString &templSpec) const
3414{
3415 int distance=0;
3416 //printf("isBaseClass(cd=%s) looking for %s templSpec=%s\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(bcd->name()),qPrint(templSpec));
3417 for (const auto &bclass : baseClasses())
3418 {
3419 const ClassDef *ccd = bclass.classDef;
3420 if (!followInstances && ccd->templateMaster())
3421 {
3422 ccd=ccd->templateMaster();
3423 }
3424 if (ccd==bcd && (templSpec.isEmpty() || templSpec==bclass.templSpecifiers))
3425 {
3426 distance=1;
3427 break; // no shorter path possible
3428 }
3429 else
3430 {
3431 int d = ccd->isBaseClass(bcd,followInstances,templSpec);
3432 if (d>256)
3433 {
3434 err("Possible recursive class relation while inside %s and looking for base class %s\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(bcd->name()));
3435 return 0;
3436 }
3437 else if (d>0) // path found
3438 {
3439 if (distance==0 || d+1<distance) // update if no path found yet or shorter path found
3440 {
3441 distance=d+1;
3442 }
3443 }
3444 }
3445 }
3446 return distance;
3447}

3449//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3450
3451bool ClassDefImpl::isSubClass(ClassDef *cd,int level) const
3452{
3453 bool found=FALSE;
3454 if (level>256)
3455 {
3456 err("Possible recursive class relation while inside %s and looking for derived class %s\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(cd->name()));
3457 return FALSE;
3458 }
3459 for (const auto &iscd : subClasses())
3460 {
3461 ClassDef *ccd=iscd.classDef;
3462 found = (ccd==cd) || ccd->isSubClass(cd,level+1);
3463 if (found) break;
3464 }
3465 return found;
3466}

3477/*!
3478 * recursively merges the 'all members' lists of a class base
3479 * with that of this class. Must only be called for classes without
3480 * subclasses!
3481 */
3482void ClassDefImpl::mergeMembers()
3483{
3484 if (m_impl->membersMerged) return;
3485
3486 //bool optimizeOutputForJava = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_JAVA);
3487 //bool vhdlOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_VHDL);
3488 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
3489 QCString sep=getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang,TRUE);
3490 uint sepLen = sep.length();
3491
3492 m_impl->membersMerged=TRUE;
3493 //printf(" mergeMembers for %s\n",qPrint(name()));
3494 bool inlineInheritedMembers = Config_getBool(INLINE_INHERITED_MEMB);
3495 bool extractPrivate = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_PRIVATE);
3496 for (const auto &bcd : baseClasses())
3497 {
3498 ClassDefMutable *bClass=toClassDefMutable(bcd.classDef);
3499 if (bClass)
3500 {
3501 // merge the members in the base class of this inheritance branch first
3502 bClass->mergeMembers();
3503 if (bClass->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Python) continue; // python does not have member overloading, see issue 8480
3504
3505 const MemberNameInfoLinkedMap &srcMnd = bClass->memberNameInfoLinkedMap();
3506 MemberNameInfoLinkedMap &dstMnd = m_impl->allMemberNameInfoLinkedMap;
3507
3508 for (auto &srcMni : srcMnd)
3509 {
3510 //printf(" Base member name %s\n",srcMni->memberName());
3511 MemberNameInfo *dstMni;
3512 if ((dstMni=dstMnd.find(srcMni->memberName())))
3513 // a member with that name is already in the class.
3514 // the member may hide or reimplement the one in the sub class
3515 // or there may be another path to the base class that is already
3516 // visited via another branch in the class hierarchy.
3517 {
3518 for (auto &srcMi : *srcMni)
3519 {
3520 MemberDef *srcMd = srcMi->memberDef();
3521 bool found=FALSE;
3522 bool ambiguous=FALSE;
3523 bool hidden=FALSE;
3524 const ClassDef *srcCd = srcMd->getClassDef();
3525 for (auto &dstMi : *dstMni)
3526 {
3527 const MemberDef *dstMd = dstMi->memberDef();
3528 if (srcMd!=dstMd) // different members
3529 {
3530 const ClassDef *dstCd = dstMd->getClassDef();
3531 //printf(" Is %s a base class of %s?\n",qPrint(srcCd->name()),qPrint(dstCd->name()));
3532 if (srcCd==dstCd || dstCd->isBaseClass(srcCd,TRUE))
3533 // member is in the same or a base class
3534 {
3535 ArgumentList &srcAl = const_cast<ArgumentList&>(srcMd->argumentList());
3536 ArgumentList &dstAl = const_cast<ArgumentList&>(dstMd->argumentList());
3537 found=matchArguments2(
3538 srcMd->getOuterScope(),srcMd->getFileDef(),&srcAl,
3539 dstMd->getOuterScope(),dstMd->getFileDef(),&dstAl,
3540 TRUE,getLanguage()
3541 );
3542 //printf(" Yes, matching (%s<->%s): %d\n",
3543 // qPrint(argListToString(srcMd->argumentList())),
3544 // qPrint(argListToString(dstMd->argumentList())),
3545 // found);
3546 hidden = hidden || !found;
3547 }
3548 else // member is in a non base class => multiple inheritance
3549 // using the same base class.
3550 {
3551 //printf("$$ Existing member %s %s add scope %s\n",
3552 // qPrint(dstMi->ambiguityResolutionScope),
3553 // qPrint(dstMd->name()),
3554 // qPrint(dstMi->scopePath.left(dstMi->scopePath.find("::")+2));
3555
3556 QCString scope=dstMi->scopePath().left(dstMi->scopePath().find(sep)+sepLen);
3557 if (scope!=dstMi->ambiguityResolutionScope().left(scope.length()))
3558 {
3559 dstMi->setAmbiguityResolutionScope(scope+dstMi->ambiguityResolutionScope());
3560 }
3561 ambiguous=TRUE;
3562 }
3563 }
3564 else // same members
3565 {
3566 // do not add if base class is virtual or
3567 // if scope paths are equal or
3568 // if base class is an interface (and thus implicitly virtual).
3569 //printf("same member found srcMi->virt=%d dstMi->virt=%d\n",srcMi->virt,dstMi->virt);
3570 if ((srcMi->virt()!=Specifier::Normal && dstMi->virt()!=Specifier::Normal) ||
3571 bClass->name()+sep+srcMi->scopePath() == dstMi->scopePath() ||
3572 dstMd->getClassDef()->compoundType()==Interface
3573 )
3574 {
3575 found=TRUE;
3576 }
3577 else // member can be reached via multiple paths in the
3578 // inheritance tree
3579 {
3580 //printf("$$ Existing member %s %s add scope %s\n",
3581 // qPrint(dstMi->ambiguityResolutionScope),
3582 // qPrint(dstMd->name()),
3583 // qPrint(dstMi->scopePath.left(dstMi->scopePath.find("::")+2));
3584
3585 QCString scope=dstMi->scopePath().left(dstMi->scopePath().find(sep)+sepLen);
3586 if (scope!=dstMi->ambiguityResolutionScope().left(scope.length()))
3587 {
3588 dstMi->setAmbiguityResolutionScope(dstMi->ambiguityResolutionScope()+scope);
3589 }
3590 ambiguous=TRUE;
3591 }
3592 }
3593 if (found) break;
3594 }
3595 //printf("member %s::%s hidden %d ambiguous %d srcMi->ambigClass=%p\n",
3596 // qPrint(srcCd->name()),qPrint(srcMd->name()),hidden,ambiguous,srcMi->ambigClass);
3597
3598 // TODO: fix the case where a member is hidden by inheritance
3599 // of a member with the same name but with another prototype,
3600 // while there is more than one path to the member in the
3601 // base class due to multiple inheritance. In this case
3602 // it seems that the member is not reachable by prefixing a
3603 // scope name either (according to my compiler). Currently,
3604 // this case is shown anyway.
3605 if (!found && srcMd->protection()!=Protection::Private && !srcMd->isFriend())
3606 {
3607 Protection prot = srcMd->protection();
3608 if (bcd.prot==Protection::Protected && prot==Protection::Public)
3609 {
3610 prot = bcd.prot;
3611 }
3612 else if (bcd.prot==Protection::Private)
3613 {
3614 prot = bcd.prot;
3615 }
3616
3617 if (inlineInheritedMembers)
3618 {
3619 if (!isStandardFunc(srcMd))
3620 {
3621 //printf(" insertMember '%s'\n",qPrint(srcMd->name()));
3622 internalInsertMember(srcMd,prot,FALSE);
3623 }
3624 }
3625
3626 Specifier virt=srcMi->virt();
3627 if (virt==Specifier::Normal && bcd.virt!=Specifier::Normal) virt=bcd.virt;
3628
3629 std::unique_ptr<MemberInfo> newMi = std::make_unique<MemberInfo>(srcMd,prot,virt,TRUE);
3630 newMi->setScopePath(bClass->name()+sep+srcMi->scopePath());
3631 if (ambiguous)
3632 {
3633 //printf("$$ New member %s %s add scope %s::\n",
3634 // qPrint(srcMi->ambiguityResolutionScope),
3635 // qPrint(srcMd->name()),
3636 // qPrint(bClass->name()));
3637
3638 QCString scope=bClass->name()+sep;
3639 if (scope!=srcMi->ambiguityResolutionScope().left(scope.length()))
3640 {
3641 newMi->setAmbiguityResolutionScope(scope+srcMi->ambiguityResolutionScope());
3642 }
3643 }
3644 if (hidden)
3645 {
3646 if (srcMi->ambigClass()==0)
3647 {
3648 newMi->setAmbigClass(bClass);
3649 newMi->setAmbiguityResolutionScope(bClass->name()+sep);
3650 }
3651 else
3652 {
3653 newMi->setAmbigClass(srcMi->ambigClass());
3654 newMi->setAmbiguityResolutionScope(srcMi->ambigClass()->name()+sep);
3655 }
3656 }
3657 dstMni->push_back(std::move(newMi));
3658 }
3659 }
3660 }
3661 else // base class has a member that is not in the sub class => copy
3662 {
3663 // create a deep copy of the list (only the MemberInfo's will be
3664 // copied, not the actual MemberDef's)
3665 MemberNameInfo *newMni = dstMnd.add(srcMni->memberName());
3666
3667 // copy the member(s) from the base to the sub class
3668 for (auto &mi : *srcMni)
3669 {
3670 if (!mi->memberDef()->isFriend()) // don't inherit friends
3671 {
3672 Protection prot = mi->prot();
3673 if (bcd.prot==Protection::Protected)
3674 {
3675 if (prot==Protection::Public) prot=Protection::Protected;
3676 }
3677 else if (bcd.prot==Protection::Private)
3678 {
3679 prot=Protection::Private;
3680 }
3681 //printf("%s::%s: prot=%d bcd.prot=%d result=%d\n",
3682 // qPrint(name()),qPrint(mi->memberDef->name()),mi->prot,
3683 // bcd.prot,prot);
3684
3685 if (prot!=Protection::Private || extractPrivate)
3686 {
3687 Specifier virt=mi->virt();
3688 if (virt==Specifier::Normal && bcd.virt!=Specifier::Normal) virt=bcd.virt;
3689
3690 if (inlineInheritedMembers)
3691 {
3692 if (!isStandardFunc(mi->memberDef()))
3693 {
3694 //printf(" insertMember '%s'\n",qPrint(mi->memberDef->name()));
3695 internalInsertMember(mi->memberDef(),prot,FALSE);
3696 }
3697 }
3698 //printf("Adding!\n");
3699 std::unique_ptr<MemberInfo> newMi = std::make_unique<MemberInfo>(mi->memberDef(),prot,virt,TRUE);
3700 newMi->setScopePath(bClass->name()+sep+mi->scopePath());
3701 newMi->setAmbigClass(mi->ambigClass());
3702 newMi->setAmbiguityResolutionScope(mi->ambiguityResolutionScope());
3703 newMni->push_back(std::move(newMi));
3704 }
3705 }
3706 }
3707 }
3708 }
3709 }
3710 }
3711 //printf(" end mergeMembers\n");
3712}

3714//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3715
3716/*! Merges the members of a Objective-C category into this class.
3717 */
3718void ClassDefImpl::mergeCategory(ClassDef *cat)
3719{
3720 ClassDefMutable *category = toClassDefMutable(cat);
3721 if (category)
3722 {
3723 bool extractLocalMethods = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_LOCAL_METHODS);
3724 bool makePrivate = category->isLocal();
3725 // in case extract local methods is not enabled we don't add the methods
3726 // of the category in case it is defined in the .m file.
3727 if (makePrivate && !extractLocalMethods) return;
3728 bool isExtension = category->isExtension();
3729
3730 category->setCategoryOf(this);
3731 if (isExtension)
3732 {
3733 category->setArtificial(TRUE);
3734
3735 // copy base classes/protocols from extension
3736 for (const auto &bcd : category->baseClasses())
3737 {
3738 insertBaseClass(bcd.classDef,bcd.usedName,bcd.prot,bcd.virt,bcd.templSpecifiers);
3739 // correct bcd.classDef so that they do no longer derive from
3740 // category, but from this class!
3741 BaseClassList scl = bcd.classDef->subClasses();
3742 for (auto &scd : scl)
3743 {
3744 if (scd.classDef==category)
3745 {
3746 scd.classDef=this;
3747 }
3748 }
3749 bcd.classDef->updateSubClasses(scl);
3750 }
3751 }
3752 // make methods private for categories defined in the .m file
3753 //printf("%s::mergeCategory makePrivate=%d\n",qPrint(name()),makePrivate);
3754
3755 const MemberNameInfoLinkedMap &srcMnd = category->memberNameInfoLinkedMap();
3756 MemberNameInfoLinkedMap &dstMnd = m_impl->allMemberNameInfoLinkedMap;
3757
3758 for (auto &srcMni : srcMnd)
3759 {
3760 MemberNameInfo *dstMni=dstMnd.find(srcMni->memberName());
3761 if (dstMni) // method is already defined in the class
3762 {
3763 //printf("Existing member %s\n",srcMni->memberName());
3764 auto &dstMi = dstMni->front();
3765 auto &srcMi = srcMni->front();
3766 if (srcMi && dstMi)
3767 {
3768 MemberDefMutable *smdm = toMemberDefMutable(srcMi->memberDef());
3769 MemberDefMutable *dmdm = toMemberDefMutable(dstMi->memberDef());
3770 if (smdm && dmdm)
3771 {
3772 combineDeclarationAndDefinition(smdm,dmdm);
3773 dmdm->setCategory(category);
3774 dmdm->setCategoryRelation(smdm);
3775 smdm->setCategoryRelation(dmdm);
3776 }
3777 }
3778 }
3779 else // new method name
3780 {
3781 //printf("New member %s\n",srcMni->memberName());
3782 // create a deep copy of the list
3783 MemberNameInfo *newMni = dstMnd.add(srcMni->memberName());
3784
3785 // copy the member(s) from the category to this class
3786 for (auto &mi : *srcMni)
3787 {
3788 //printf("Adding '%s'\n",qPrint(mi->memberDef->name()));
3789 Protection prot = mi->prot();
3790 //if (makePrivate) prot = Private;
3791 std::unique_ptr<MemberDefMutable> newMd { toMemberDefMutable(mi->memberDef()->deepCopy()) };
3792 if (newMd)
3793 {
3794 //printf("Copying member %s\n",qPrint(mi->memberDef->name()));
3795 newMd->moveTo(this);
3796
3797 std::unique_ptr<MemberInfo> newMi=std::make_unique<MemberInfo>(newMd.get(),prot,mi->virt(),mi->inherited());
3798 newMi->setScopePath(mi->scopePath());
3799 newMi->setAmbigClass(mi->ambigClass());
3800 newMi->setAmbiguityResolutionScope(mi->ambiguityResolutionScope());
3801 newMni->push_back(std::move(newMi));
3802
3803 // also add the newly created member to the global members list
3804
3805 QCString name = newMd->name();
3806 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(name);
3807
3808 if (newMd)
3809 {
3810 newMd->setCategory(category);
3811 newMd->setCategoryRelation(mi->memberDef());
3812 }
3813 MemberDefMutable *mdm = toMemberDefMutable(mi->memberDef());
3814 if (mdm)
3815 {
3816 mdm->setCategoryRelation(newMd.get());
3817 }
3818 if (newMd && (makePrivate || isExtension))
3819 {
3820 newMd->makeImplementationDetail();
3821 }
3822 internalInsertMember(newMd.get(),prot,FALSE);
3823 mn->push_back(std::move(newMd));
3824 }
3825 }
3826 }
3827 }
3828 }
3829}

3834 Protection prot)
3835{

3837 bool umlLook = Config_getBool(UML_LOOK);
3838 if (prot==Protection::Private && !extractPrivate) return;
3839 //printf("%s::addUsedClass(%s,%s)\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(cd->name()),accessName);
3840
3841 auto it = std::find_if(m_impl->usesImplClassList.begin(),
3842 m_impl->usesImplClassList.end(),
3843 [&cd](const auto &ucd) { return ucd.classDef==cd; });
3844 if (it==m_impl->usesImplClassList.end())
3845 {
3846 m_impl->usesImplClassList.emplace_back(cd);
3847 //printf("Adding used class %s to class %s via accessor %s\n",
3848 // qPrint(cd->name()),qPrint(name()),accessName);
3849 it = m_impl->usesImplClassList.end()-1;
3850 }
3851 QCString acc = accessName;
3852 if (umlLook)
3853 {
3854 switch(prot)
3855 {
3856 case Protection::Public: acc.prepend("+"); break;
3857 case Protection::Private: acc.prepend("-"); break;
3858 case Protection::Protected: acc.prepend("#"); break;
3859 case Protection::Package: acc.prepend("~"); break;
3860 }
3861 }
3862 (*it).addAccessor(acc);
3863}

3932QCString ClassDefImpl::getOutputFileBase() const
3933{
3934 bool inlineGroupedClasses = Config_getBool(INLINE_GROUPED_CLASSES);
3935 bool inlineSimpleClasses = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
3936 if (!Doxygen::generatingXmlOutput)
3937 {
3938 Definition *scope=0;
3939 if (inlineGroupedClasses && !partOfGroups().empty())
3940 {
3941 // point to the group that embeds this class
3942 return partOfGroups().front()->getOutputFileBase();
3943 }
3944 else if (inlineSimpleClasses && m_impl->isSimple && !partOfGroups().empty())
3945 {
3946 // point to simple struct inside a group
3947 return partOfGroups().front()->getOutputFileBase();
3948 }
3949 else if (inlineSimpleClasses && m_impl->isSimple && (scope=getOuterScope()))
3950 {
3951 if (scope==Doxygen::globalScope && getFileDef() && getFileDef()->isLinkableInProject()) // simple struct embedded in file
3952 {
3953 return getFileDef()->getOutputFileBase();
3954 }
3955 else if (scope->isLinkableInProject()) // simple struct embedded in other container (namespace/group/class)
3956 {
3957 return getOuterScope()->getOutputFileBase();
3958 }
3959 }
3960 }
3961 if (m_impl->templateMaster)
3962 {
3963 // point to the template of which this class is an instance
3964 return m_impl->templateMaster->getOutputFileBase();
3965 }
3966 return m_impl->fileName;

4021ClassDef *ClassDefImpl::insertTemplateInstance(const QCString &fileName,
4022 int startLine, int startColumn, const QCString &templSpec,bool &freshInstance) const
4023{
4024 freshInstance = FALSE;
4025 auto it = std::find_if(m_impl->templateInstances.begin(),
4026 m_impl->templateInstances.end(),
4027 [&templSpec](const auto &ti) { return templSpec==ti.templSpec; });
4028 ClassDefMutable *templateClass=0;
4029 if (it!=m_impl->templateInstances.end())
4030 {
4031 templateClass = toClassDefMutable((*it).classDef);
4032 }
4033 if (templateClass==0)
4034 {
4035 QCString tcname = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(localName()+templSpec);
4036 Debug::print(Debug::Classes,0," New template instance class '%s''%s' inside '%s' hidden=%d\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(templSpec),qPrint(name()),isHidden());
4037
4038 ClassDef *foundCd = Doxygen::classLinkedMap->find(tcname);
4039 if (foundCd)
4040 {
4041 return foundCd;
4042 }
4043 templateClass =
4044 toClassDefMutable(
4045 Doxygen::classLinkedMap->add(tcname,
4046 std::unique_ptr<ClassDef>(
4047 new ClassDefImpl(fileName,startLine,startColumn,tcname,ClassDef::Class))));
4048 if (templateClass)
4049 {
4050 templateClass->setTemplateMaster(this);
4051 templateClass->setOuterScope(getOuterScope());
4052 templateClass->setHidden(isHidden());
4053 templateClass->setArtificial(isArtificial());
4054 m_impl->templateInstances.push_back(TemplateInstanceDef(templSpec,templateClass));
4055
4056 // also add nested classes
4057 for (const auto &innerCd : m_impl->innerClasses)
4058 {
4059 QCString innerName = tcname+"::"+innerCd->localName();
4060 ClassDefMutable *innerClass =
4061 toClassDefMutable(
4062 Doxygen::classLinkedMap->add(innerName,
4063 std::unique_ptr<ClassDef>(
4064 new ClassDefImpl(fileName,startLine,startColumn,innerName,ClassDef::Class))));
4065 if (innerClass)
4066 {
4067 templateClass->addInnerCompound(innerClass);
4068 innerClass->setOuterScope(templateClass);
4069 innerClass->setHidden(isHidden());
4070 innerClass->setArtificial(TRUE);
4071 }
4072 }
4073 freshInstance=TRUE;
4074 }
4075 }
4076 return templateClass;
4077}

4221const MemberDef *ClassDefImpl::getMemberByName(const QCString &name) const
4222{
4223 const MemberDef *xmd = 0;
4224 MemberNameInfo *mni = m_impl->allMemberNameInfoLinkedMap.find(name);
4225 if (mni)
4226 {
4227 const int maxInheritanceDepth = 100000;
4228 int mdist=maxInheritanceDepth;
4229 for (auto &mi : *mni)
4230 {
4231 const ClassDef *mcd=mi->memberDef()->getClassDef();
4232 int m=minClassDistance(this,mcd);
4233 //printf("found member in %s linkable=%d m=%d\n",
4234 // qPrint(mcd->name()),mcd->isLinkable(),m);
4235 if (m<mdist && mcd->isLinkable())
4236 {
4237 mdist=m;
4238 xmd=mi->memberDef();
4239 }
4240 }
4241 }
4242 //printf("getMemberByName(%s)=%p\n",qPrint(name),xmd);
4243 return xmd;
4244}

4263void ClassDefImpl::addMemberToList(MemberListType lt,MemberDef *md,bool isBrief)
4264{
4265 bool sortBriefDocs = Config_getBool(SORT_BRIEF_DOCS);
4266 bool sortMemberDocs = Config_getBool(SORT_MEMBER_DOCS);
4267 const auto &ml = m_impl->memberLists.get(lt,MemberListContainer::Class);
4268 ml->setNeedsSorting((isBrief && sortBriefDocs) || (!isBrief && sortMemberDocs));
4269 ml->push_back(md);
4270
4271 // for members in the declaration lists we set the section, needed for member grouping
4272 if ((ml->listType()&MemberListType_detailedLists)==0)
4273 {
4274 MemberDefMutable *mdm = toMemberDefMutable(md);
4275 if (mdm)
4276 {
4277 mdm->setSectionList(this,ml.get());
4278 }
4279 }

4282void ClassDefImpl::sortMemberLists()
4283{
4284 for (auto &ml : m_impl->memberLists)
4285 {
4286 if (ml->needsSorting()) { ml->sort(); ml->setNeedsSorting(FALSE); }
4287 }
4288 std::sort(m_impl->innerClasses.begin(),
4289 m_impl->innerClasses.end(),
4290 [](const auto &c1,const auto &c2)
4291 {
4292 return Config_getBool(SORT_BY_SCOPE_NAME) ?
4293 qstricmp(c1->name(), c2->name() )<0 :
4294 qstricmp(c1->className(), c2->className())<0 ;
4295 });
4296}
4297
4298int ClassDefImpl::countMemberDeclarations(MemberListType lt,const ClassDef *inheritedFrom,
4299 int lt2,bool invert,bool showAlways,ClassDefSet &visitedClasses) const
4300{
4301 //printf("%s: countMemberDeclarations for %d and %d\n",qPrint(name()),lt,lt2);
4302 int count=0;
4303 MemberList * ml = getMemberList(lt);
4304 MemberList * ml2 = getMemberList(static_cast<MemberListType>(lt2));
4305 if (getLanguage()!=SrcLangExt_VHDL) // use specific declarations function
4306 {
4307 if (ml)
4308 {
4309 count+=ml->numDecMembers();
4310 //printf("-> ml=%d\n",ml->numDecMembers());
4311 }
4312 if (ml2)
4313 {
4314 count+=ml2->numDecMembers();
4315 //printf("-> ml2=%d\n",ml2->numDecMembers());
4316 }
4317 // also include grouped members that have their own section in the class (see bug 722759)
4318 if (inheritedFrom)
4319 {
4320 for (const auto &mg : m_impl->memberGroups)
4321 {
4322 count+=mg->countGroupedInheritedMembers(lt);
4323 if (lt2!=-1) count+=mg->countGroupedInheritedMembers(static_cast<MemberListType>(lt2));
4324 }
4325 }
4326 bool inlineInheritedMembers = Config_getBool(INLINE_INHERITED_MEMB);
4327 if (!inlineInheritedMembers) // show inherited members as separate lists
4328 {
4329 count+=countInheritedDecMembers(lt,inheritedFrom,invert,showAlways,visitedClasses);
4330 }
4331 }
4332 //printf("-> %d\n",count);
4333 return count;
4334}

4376int ClassDefImpl::countInheritedDecMembers(MemberListType lt,
4377 const ClassDef *inheritedFrom,bool invert,bool showAlways,
4378 ClassDefSet &visitedClasses) const
4379{
4380 int inhCount = 0;
4381 int count = countMembersIncludingGrouped(lt,inheritedFrom,FALSE);
4382 bool process = count>0;
4383 //printf("%s: countInheritedDecMembers: lt=%d process=%d count=%d invert=%d\n",
4384 // qPrint(name()),lt,process,count,invert);
4385 if ((process^invert) || showAlways)
4386 {
4387 for (const auto &ibcd : m_impl->inherits)
4388 {
4389 ClassDefMutable *icd=toClassDefMutable(ibcd.classDef);
4390 int lt1,lt2;
4391 if (icd && icd->isLinkable())
4392 {
4393 convertProtectionLevel(lt,ibcd.prot,&lt1,&lt2);
4394 //printf("%s: convert %d->(%d,%d) prot=%d\n",
4395 // qPrint(icd->name()),lt,lt1,lt2,ibcd->prot);
4396 if (visitedClasses.find(icd)==visitedClasses.end())
4397 {
4398 visitedClasses.insert(icd); // guard for multiple virtual inheritance
4399 if (lt1!=-1)
4400 {
4401 inhCount+=icd->countMemberDeclarations(static_cast<MemberListType>(lt1),inheritedFrom,lt2,FALSE,TRUE,visitedClasses);
4402 }
4403 }
4404 }
4405 }
4406 }
4407 return inhCount;
4408}

4467int ClassDefImpl::countMembersIncludingGrouped(MemberListType lt,
4468 const ClassDef *inheritedFrom,bool additional) const
4469{
4470 int count=0;
4471 MemberList *ml = getMemberList(lt);
4472 if (ml)
4473 {
4474 count=ml->countInheritableMembers(inheritedFrom);
4475 }
4476 //printf("%s:countMembersIncludingGrouped: count=%d\n",qPrint(name()),count);
4477 for (const auto &mg : m_impl->memberGroups)
4478 {
4479 bool hasOwnSection = !mg->allMembersInSameSection() ||
4480 !m_impl->subGrouping; // group is in its own section
4481 if ((additional && hasOwnSection) || (!additional && !hasOwnSection))
4482 {
4483 count+=mg->countGroupedInheritedMembers(lt);
4484 }
4485 }
4486 //printf("%s:countMembersIncludingGrouped(lt=%d,%s)=%d\n",
4487 // qPrint(name()),lt,ml?qPrint(ml->listTypeAsString(ml->listType())):"<none>",count);
4488 return count;
4489}

4492void ClassDefImpl::writeInheritedMemberDeclarations(OutputList &ol,ClassDefSet &visitedClasses,
4493 MemberListType lt,int lt2,const QCString &title,
4494 const ClassDef *inheritedFrom,bool invert,bool showAlways) const
4495{
4496 int count = countMembersIncludingGrouped(lt,inheritedFrom,FALSE);
4497 bool process = count>0;
4498 //printf("%s: writeInheritedMemberDec: lt=%d process=%d invert=%d always=%d\n",
4499 // qPrint(name()),lt,process,invert,showAlways);
4500 if ((process^invert) || showAlways)
4501 {
4502 for (const auto &ibcd : m_impl->inherits)
4503 {
4504 ClassDefMutable *icd=toClassDefMutable(ibcd.classDef);
4505 if (icd && icd->isLinkable())
4506 {
4507 int lt1,lt3;
4508 convertProtectionLevel(lt,ibcd.prot,&lt1,&lt3);
4509 if (lt2==-1 && lt3!=-1)
4510 {
4511 lt2=lt3;
4512 }
4513 //printf("%s:convert %d->(%d,%d) prot=%d\n",qPrint(icd->name()),lt,lt1,lt2,ibcd->prot);
4514 if (visitedClasses.find(icd)==visitedClasses.end())
4515 {
4516 visitedClasses.insert(icd); // guard for multiple virtual inheritance
4517 if (lt1!=-1)
4518 {
4519 icd->writeMemberDeclarations(ol,visitedClasses,static_cast<MemberListType>(lt1),
4520 title,QCString(),FALSE,inheritedFrom,lt2,FALSE,TRUE);
4521 }
4522 }
4523 else
4524 {
4525 //printf("%s: class already visited!\n",qPrint(icd->name()));
4526 }
4527 }
4528 }
4529 }
4530}

4532void ClassDefImpl::writeMemberDeclarations(OutputList &ol,ClassDefSet &visitedClasses,
4533 MemberListType lt,const QCString &title,
4534 const QCString &subTitle,bool showInline,const ClassDef *inheritedFrom,int lt2,
4535 bool invert,bool showAlways) const
4536{
4537 //printf("%s: ClassDefImpl::writeMemberDeclarations lt=%d lt2=%d\n",qPrint(name()),lt,lt2);
4538 MemberList * ml = getMemberList(lt);
4539 MemberList * ml2 = getMemberList(static_cast<MemberListType>(lt2));
4540 if (getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_VHDL) // use specific declarations function
4541 {
4542 static const ClassDef *cdef;
4543 if (cdef!=this)
4544 { // only one inline link
4545 VhdlDocGen::writeInlineClassLink(this,ol);
4546 cdef=this;
4547 }
4548 if (ml)
4549 {
4550 VhdlDocGen::writeVhdlDeclarations(ml,ol,0,this,0,0);
4551 }
4552 }
4553 else
4554 {
4555 //printf("%s::writeMemberDeclarations(%s) ml=%p ml2=%p\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(title),ml,ml2);
4556 QCString tt = title, st = subTitle;
4557 if (ml)
4558 {
4559 //printf(" writeDeclaration type=%d count=%d\n",lt,ml->numDecMembers());
4560 ml->writeDeclarations(ol,this,0,0,0,tt,st,FALSE,showInline,inheritedFrom,lt);
4561 tt.resize(0);
4562 st.resize(0);
4563 }
4564 if (ml2)
4565 {
4566 //printf(" writeDeclaration type=%d count=%d\n",lt2,ml2->numDecMembers());
4567 ml2->writeDeclarations(ol,this,0,0,0,tt,st,FALSE,showInline,inheritedFrom,lt);
4568 }
4569 bool inlineInheritedMembers = Config_getBool(INLINE_INHERITED_MEMB);
4570 if (!inlineInheritedMembers) // show inherited members as separate lists
4571 {
4572 writeInheritedMemberDeclarations(ol,visitedClasses,lt,lt2,title,
4573 inheritedFrom ? inheritedFrom : this,
4574 invert,showAlways);
4575 }
4576 }
4577}

4579void ClassDefImpl::addGroupedInheritedMembers(OutputList &ol,MemberListType lt,

4581{
4582 //printf("** %s::addGroupedInheritedMembers(%p) inheritId=%s\n",qPrint(name()),m_impl->memberGroupSDict,qPrint(inheritId));
4583 for (const auto &mg : m_impl->memberGroups)
4584 {

4586 {
4587 mg->addGroupedInheritedMembers(ol,this,lt,inheritedFrom,inheritId);
4588 }

4879
4880bool ClassDefImpl::isEmbeddedInOuterScope() const
4881{
4882 bool inlineGroupedClasses = Config_getBool(INLINE_GROUPED_CLASSES);
4883 bool inlineSimpleClasses = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
4884
4885 Definition *container = getOuterScope();
4886
4887 bool containerLinkable =
4888 container &&
4889 (
4890 (container==Doxygen::globalScope && getFileDef() && getFileDef()->isLinkableInProject()) || // global class in documented file
4891 container->isLinkableInProject() // class in documented scope
4892 );
4893
4894 // inline because of INLINE_GROUPED_CLASSES=YES ?
4895 bool b1 = (inlineGroupedClasses && !partOfGroups().empty()); // a grouped class
4896 // inline because of INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS=YES ?
4897 bool b2 = (inlineSimpleClasses && m_impl->isSimple && // a simple class
4898 (containerLinkable || // in a documented container
4899 !partOfGroups().empty() // or part of a group
4900 )
4901 );
4902 //printf("%s::isEmbeddedInOuterScope(): inlineGroupedClasses=%d "
4903 // "inlineSimpleClasses=%d partOfGroups()=%p m_impl->isSimple=%d "
4904 // "getOuterScope()=%s b1=%d b2=%d\n",
4905 // qPrint(name()),inlineGroupedClasses,inlineSimpleClasses,
4906 // partOfGroups().pointer(),m_impl->isSimple,getOuterScope()?qPrint(getOuterScope()->name()):"<none>",b1,b2);
4907 return b1 || b2; // either reason will do
4908}

5130//----------------------------------------------------------------------
5131// recursive function that returns the number of branches in the
5132// inheritance tree that the base class 'bcd' is below the class 'cd'
5133
5134int minClassDistance(const ClassDef *cd,const ClassDef *bcd,int level)
5135{
5136 const int maxInheritanceDepth = 100000;
5137 if (bcd->categoryOf()) // use class that is being extended in case of
5138 // an Objective-C category
5139 {
5140 bcd=bcd->categoryOf();
5141 }
5142 if (cd==bcd) return level;
5143 if (level==256)
5144 {
5145 warn_uncond("class %s seem to have a recursive "
5146 "inheritance relation!\n",qPrint(cd->name()));
5147 return -1;
5148 }
5149 int m=maxInheritanceDepth;
5150 for (const auto &bcdi : cd->baseClasses())
5151 {
5152 int mc=minClassDistance(bcdi.classDef,bcd,level+1);
5153 if (mc<m) m=mc;
5154 if (m<0) break;
5155 }
5156 return m;
5157}
5158
5159Protection classInheritedProtectionLevel(const ClassDef *cd,const ClassDef *bcd,Protection prot,int level)
5160{
5161 if (bcd->categoryOf()) // use class that is being extended in case of
5162 // an Objective-C category
5163 {
5164 bcd=bcd->categoryOf();
5165 }
5166 if (cd==bcd)
5167 {
5168 goto exit;
5169 }
5170 if (level==256)
5171 {
5172 err("Internal inconsistency: found class %s seem to have a recursive "
5173 "inheritance relation! Please send a bug report to doxygen@gmail.com\n",qPrint(cd->name()));
5174 }
5175 else if (prot!=Protection::Private)
5176 {
5177 for (const auto &bcdi : cd->baseClasses())
5178 {
5179 Protection baseProt = classInheritedProtectionLevel(bcdi.classDef,bcd,bcdi.prot,level+1);
5180 if (baseProt==Protection::Private) prot=Protection::Private;
5181 else if (baseProt==Protection::Protected) prot=Protection::Protected;
5182 }
5183 }
5184exit:
5185 //printf("classInheritedProtectionLevel(%s,%s)=%d\n",qPrint(cd->name()),qPrint(bcd->name()),prot);
5186 return prot;
5187}
